TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Find all solutions of the equation \( \sin^2 x = 2 \sin x + 3. \)
$BR
The answer is \(A+Bk\pi\) where \(k\) is any integer and \(0<A<2\pi\),
$BR
\( A= \) \{ans_rule(15)\}, \( B= \) \{ans_rule(15)\}.
$BR
EOT

$ans1= 3*$PI/2;
$ans2= 2;

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

